25|$|The {{title of}} the short-story {{collection}} Everything That Rises Must Converge by <b>Flannery</b> <b>O'Connor</b> is a reference to Teilhard's work. The American novelist Don DeLillo's 2010 novel Point Omega borrows its title {{and some of its}} ideas from Teilhard de Chardin. Robert Wright, in his book , compares his own naturalistic thesis that biological and cultural evolution are directional and, possibly, purposeful, with Teilhard's ideas.|$|E
